{
    "id": "welcome/connect-github",
    "title": "Connect GitHub",
    "description": "Link your GitHub account to enable cloud sync and quest submissions.",
    "image": "/assets/quests/connect_github_integration.jpg",
    "npc": "/assets/npc/dChat.jpg",
    "start": "start",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "id": "start",
            "text": "GitHub keeps your progress portable: cloud sync, quest submissions, and safer backups across devices. We'll connect with a classic personal access token (PAT).",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "steps",
                    "text": "Show me the steps"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-1",
                    "text": "Quiz me first"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "steps",
            "text": "GitHub → Settings → Developer settings → Personal access tokens → Tokens (classic) → Generate new token (classic). Select repo + gist, set an expiration, copy the token once, then paste it into /cloudsync and click Save.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "safety",
                    "text": "Got it."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "safety",
            "text": "Treat your PAT as sensitive: never post it in chat or commits. If it leaks, revoke it immediately in GitHub settings.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-1",
                    "text": "Quiz time"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-1",
            "text": "What do PAT scopes control?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-2",
                    "text": "They limit what the token can access; choose only what DSPACE needs."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-1-wrong",
                    "text": "They set the token's username and display name."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-1-wrong",
                    "text": "They decide how much dUSD you can spend."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-1-wrong",
            "text": "Scopes are permissions. Pick only what you need—repo + gist are the classic scopes for DSPACE.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-1",
                    "text": "Try again"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-2",
            "text": "What's the safest way to handle your PAT?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-3",
                    "text": "Store it in /cloudsync and keep it private—never share it."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-2-wrong",
                    "text": "Paste it into a public gist so you can find it later."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-2-wrong",
                    "text": "Commit it once so CI can read it."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-2-wrong",
            "text": "Tokens are secrets. Keep them private, store them only where needed, and revoke if exposed.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-2",
                    "text": "Try again"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-3",
            "text": "What does connecting GitHub unlock in DSPACE?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-4",
                    "text": "Cloud sync, quest submissions, and progress portability."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-3-wrong",
                    "text": "Free dUSD every hour."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-3-wrong",
                    "text": "Automatic hardware shipments."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-3-wrong",
            "text": "GitHub gives you sync + submissions + portability—no freebies, just reliable backups.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-3",
                    "text": "Try again"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-4",
            "text": "Need to revoke a token? Where do you go?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "finish",
                    "text": "GitHub Settings → Developer settings → Personal access tokens."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-4-wrong",
                    "text": "Delete your DSPACE save file."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-4-wrong",
                    "text": "Ask in the DSPACE chat."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-4-wrong",
            "text": "Revocation happens in GitHub settings. You can always create a new PAT after deleting the old one.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-4",
                    "text": "Try again"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "finish",
            "text": "Great! Your GitHub account is connected. The finish button unlocks once a valid token is saved.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "finish",
                    "text": "All set!",
                    "requiresGitHub": true
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    "rewards": [
